# UPSC IAS Prep — Project Conventions

## Stack
- Frontend: Expo 51 + React Native + TypeScript (TSX) + NativeWind v4
- Backend: FastAPI + Python 3.11 + SQLAlchemy 2.0 async + Alembic
- DB: PostgreSQL 16 + Redis 7
- Auth: Firebase (Google OAuth for happy path, phone OTP + Facebook later)
- Payments: Razorpay subscriptions (full project phase)
- Deploy: Docker + Nginx + DigitalOcean

## Build Phases
- Day 1: Backend only (Steps 1-13). Goal: all APIs working at localhost:8000/docs
- Day 2: Frontend happy path (Steps 14-19). Goal: Google login → question → history
- Full Project: Admin panel UI, payments, phone OTP, deployment (Steps 20-22)

## Package Management — CRITICAL
- Python uses uv only. NEVER pip install.
- No requirements.txt. Use pyproject.toml + uv.lock.
- uv sync → installs from lockfile locally
- uv add packagename → adds new package
- uv run <command> → runs any Python command
- Docker uses: uv sync --frozen
- uv.lock must be committed to git, never in .gitignore

## Critical Backend Rules
1. Never return correct_option from GET /questions/next
   Only return it in POST /attempts/submit response
2. Option shuffling: frontend only, Fisher-Yates + useMemo([question.id])
   Backend always stores/returns original A/B/C/D keys
3. JWT: access token 15min, refresh token 30 days
   Frontend silently refreshes via axios interceptor on 401
4. All DB calls must be async (SQLAlchemy async session)
5. topic_performance uses PostgreSQL ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE upsert
6. Adaptive selection excludes questions attempted in last 7 days
7. Free plan: 5 questions/day in users.daily_questions_used
8. Admin auth: separate admin_users table, bcrypt passwords
9. Razorpay webhook: no JWT, verify X-Razorpay-Signature only
10. Always TSX not JSX. Always async/await not .then()

## Folder Locations
- Backend routers: backend/app/routers/
- Backend models: backend/app/models/models.py
- Backend schemas: backend/app/schemas/schemas.py
- Frontend screens: frontend/app/
- Frontend components: frontend/components/
- Admin panel: admin/src/
